thread.title: 2 arrested in connection to missing Ponchatoula man
thread.title_full: 2 arrested in connection to missing Ponchatoula man - FOX 8 WVUE New Orleans News, Weather, Sports, Social

author: Amber Stegall
title: 2 arrested in connection to missing Ponchatoula man
text:
PONCHATOULA, LA (WAFB) - Tangipahoa Parish Daniel Edwards reports that two arrests have been made in the disappearance of 29-year-old Seth Landry of Ponchatoula. Landry was last seen by his family on September 18, 2015.
Officials with the Tangipahoa Parish Sheriff's Office say Landry's body was found on October 21, 2015, off of Highway 43, near St. Helena Parish.
According to a news release from the sheriff's office, Landry died from an overdose.
Joshua Paul Orso, 27 of Ponchatoula and Bryan Jason Barnes, 44 have been arrested and charged with one count of negligent homicide.
This investigation is on-going.
